About this item

Smart summary

Generated by AI

The U Style Eco-Friendly 1 Subject Notebook is a 4-pack of notebooks, each with  80 sheets of college-ruled, perforated paper . The notebooks are  10.5 inches x 8.5 inches in size . The  paper is sourced from certified and sustainable forests . The  covers are made from 70% recycled materials  and printed with soy-based ink. Each notebook has  FSC-certified paper , and a portion of the purchase supports reforestation efforts. These notebooks are suitable for school, work, and home use, offering a reliable and eco-friendly option for note-taking and writing.

About this item

Product details

The U Style Eco-Friendly 1 Subject Notebooks are high-quality notebooks that are responsibly made! These notebooks have covers that are made from 70% recycled materials which are also printed with soy-based ink and have FSC-certified paper. Each notebook has 80 sheets of perforated paper, which is college ruled. There are 4 notebooks within this multipack. U Style also partners with One Tree Planted to offset our environmental impact. Together, we can restore forests, create habitats for biodiversity, and make a positive social impact around the world!
  • 4-pack of 1 subject notebook
  • Individual notebook size - 10.5 inches x 8.5 inches
  • 80 sheets of college-ruled lined paper
  • Paper is perforated for a clean, perfect tear
  • Great for school, work, and home
  • Paper is responsibly sourced from certified and sustainable forests
  • A portion of each purchase will be donated to One Tree Planted, a non-profit fighting climate change one tree at a time.

REAL QUALITY COVER TO COIL

I love everything about these notebooks to the tune of about 10 orders of the packs over the past three years at least.!! The quality coils, beautiful sturdy covers in earthy colors plus what USTYLE collections stands for! The many gel pens and fountain pen I use absolutely do not bleed through. It is the little things in life. There isn't anything USTYLE promises that it hasn't delivered. PLEASE get them back in stock! Intuition screamed hoard them. I did. Now I am panicked having only one perfectly packaged set left. Again, the coils!! They withstand it all from storing away in its plastic wrap to being stacked upon. Coils are a justifiable pet peeve of mine.
